quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  40,69,Do you not see those who dispute concerning the signs of God? How are they turned away
  40,70,"Those who reject the Book and that with which We sent our messengers, but soon will they know"
  40,71,"When the chains will be around their necks, and in the chains, they will be dragged along—"
  40,72,"In the boiling fluid, then in the fire, they will be burned"
  40,73,"Then it will be said to them, “Where are those to which you gave part worship"
  40,74,"“To other than God?” They will reply, “They have left us lost. No, we invoked nothing from the past.” So God leaves the unbelievers to stray"
  40,75,"“That is because you were accustomed to rejoicing on the earth in things other than the truth, and that you were accustomed to being insolent"
  40,76,"“Enter the gates of hell, to dwell therein, and terrible is the abode of the arrogant.”"
  40,77,"So persevere in patience, for the promise of God is true, and whether We show you some part of what We promise them, or We take your soul before that, it is to Us that they will all return"
  40,78,"We sent messengers before you. Of them there are some whose story We have related to you, and some whose story We have not related to you. It was not possible for any messenger to bring a sign except by the permission of God, but when the command of God issued, the matter was decided in truth and justice, and they perished there, those who stood on falsehood"